In #large bowl{}, mix 1/2 cup of @granulated sugar{1/2%cup}, @brown sugar{1/2%cup}, @peanut butter{1/2%cup}, @shortening{1/4%cup}, @butter{1/4%cup}, and @egg{1}.  Stir in @Gluten Free Bisquick mix{1.5%cups}.  Cover; refrigerate 1 hour or until firm.
Heat oven to 375 degrees.  In #small bowl{}, place 1/4 cup @granulated sugar{1/4%cup}.  Shape dough into 1-inch balls; roll in granulated sugar.  On ungreased #cookie sheets{}, place balls 2 inches apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light golden brown.  Immediately top each cookie with 1 @Hershey's Kiss milk chocolate{48}, pressing down firmly so cookie cracks around edge.  Remove from cookie sheets to cooling racks.